HEADWORD: Campanile
<hw>Cam`pa*ni"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>campanile</ets> bell tower, steeple, fr. It. & LL.
<ets>campana</ets> bell.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A bell tower,
esp. one built separate from a church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many of the <qex>campaniles</qex> of Italy are lofty and
magnificent structures.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Campaniliform</ent>⟦br⟧
